Generalization

The central question of machine learning theory:

How can a model perform well on unseen data?

A model should learn underlying patterns, not memorize training examples.

Overfitting vs Underfitting
Underfitting

Model is too simple.

High training error
High test error
Overfitting

Model memorizes noise.

Low training error
High test error

Goal:
Balance complexity and generalization.

Bias–Variance Tradeoff

Prediction error can be viewed as:

